00:07.540 --> 00:19.293
This is very important historically because, 
like we said, like I said before, movies, TV were

00:07.540 --> 00:19.293
glamorizing SAC. And they were getting the

00:21.015 --> 00:36.332
publicity during the 1950s as being, I guess, as 
being the elite of the armed forces. Would you

00:36.599 --> 00:38.401
agree with that? I was going to say, and probably 
rightfully so. Because, you know, this was after

00:42.886 --> 00:58.202
the war and everything was being cut back, budget 
being cut back, and get back to this old bit of

00:42.886 --> 00:58.202
during time peace where everybody fights for 
their dollar to grow the budget. And, you know, it

00:58.222 --> 01:05.830
immediately started and the Army was clamoring 
for to keep so many divisions and so many tanks and

01:06.265 --> 01:08.928
so forth. The Navy wanted to keep so many ships and 
so forth. And we Air Force wanted an air defense

01:12.692 --> 01:17.558
command as well as SAC, as well as TAC. And, you 
know, somebody had to give someplace and

01:18.378 --> 01:22.503
compromise some way. But we in the Air Force, from 
the chief on down, that's where we got the basic

01:23.044 --> 01:35.057
guidance from the chief of staff of the Air Force 
that SAC And the nuclear capability, if you will,

01:36.117 --> 01:41.944
strategic capability was top priority. And for a 
while it was a little bit hard for tactical

01:43.326 --> 01:53.800
commanders, namely air defense and tactical 
command, to swallow. See, we were trying to build

01:53.860 --> 01:56.263
up the tactical air command. I mean the air defense 
command, NORAD.

02:01.328 --> 02:03.391
Of course, this was to give warning to SAC. So you 
see, there was arguments for giving us money. We

02:06.977 --> 02:12.605
had to give warning to SAC so they could get on, so 
they could do their job. So you had a rivalry right

02:12.625 --> 02:17.272
in your arms? Rivalry is the best thing to call it, 
for the dollars. Sure. Rivalry for the dollars.

02:22.019 --> 02:25.665
And SAGE cost us billions and billions of dollars. 
SAGE? SAGE, the Automatic Guidelines. Were you

02:31.720 --> 02:34.743
yourself jealous of the Strategic Air Command? A 
little bit. Looking back now, I just plain old

02:36.545 --> 02:41.070
professional jealousy. In times I remember 
making a comment, they act like they're not even in

02:41.330 --> 02:47.456
the regular Air Force, they're a separate Air 
Force. And I think that's out of temperament and

02:47.476 --> 02:51.781
professional jealousy. Did you ever want to apply 
for a SAT? I didn't like the philosophy of command

02:58.163 --> 03:05.535
that they used in SAC. Which was? Fear.

03:11.525 --> 03:24.627
I had served

03:11.525 --> 03:24.627
under ex-SAC people in my subsequent career after 
in the latter part of my Air Force career.

03:29.939 --> 03:40.830
philosophy of command, and for a while it darn near 
demoralized the tactical

03:29.939 --> 03:40.830
aircraft. Fortunately, that commander didn't 
stay long, and so we had another typical tactical

03:40.850 --> 03:49.519
aircraft commander, John Displey, who took over 
and got things back on an even keel. And this gets

03:50.540 --> 03:54.204
into the philosophy of command maybe you want to 
talk about later on. Well, tell me about fear.

03:55.845 --> 03:59.389
Well, give me an example of that in the strategic 
air command.

04:03.031 --> 04:11.002
You do a job, if you have an accident, this man does 
that, you're fired. You're ruined. You're career

04:11.523 --> 04:12.444
is over. And you heard SAC commanders say that to a 
man? This was the philosophy of SAC. But you

04:19.515 --> 04:21.477
yourself heard that? Almost. Oh, yes.

04:29.008 --> 04:32.413
Many people in airports at that time felt that. I 
don't blame this on LeMay. Who do you blame it on?

04:37.675 --> 04:40.178
Other officers in the SAC hierarchy.

04:42.261 --> 04:43.643
I don't think that exists now. As a matter of fact,

04:43.663 --> 04:51.272
SAC has changed now, and they don't have this 
philosophy anymore. We don't have this feeling in

04:51.292 --> 04:54.216
the Air Force anymore, to my knowledge. We know the 
requirements of having SAC. There's no doubt of

04:59.543 --> 05:02.046
the puts of And now, you know, we've even got the 
intercontinental ballistic missiles, which are

05:02.633 --> 05:07.879
still part of SAC. And to prove that we were right in 
our thinking that SAC is a predominant military

05:09.101 --> 05:31.847
power in our arsenal is that the Joint Targeting 
Committee is headquartered at the SAC

05:09.101 --> 05:31.847
headquarters, the Navy and the Air Force, under 
the Commander-in-Chief of the Strategic Air

05:09.101 --> 05:31.847
Command. So he is the top man. There's no doubt 
about it. But going back to some of these things

05:39.571 --> 05:49.585
we've talked about, I think it is professional 
jealousy, but it can be expected. But it's, I don't

05:49.625 --> 05:54.452
want to say unfounded. SAC should be recognized. 
It should be glamorized. It should have gotten the

05:57.676 --> 05:58.918
money. It should have been built up. Thank God 
we've got it in the position it is right now. Thank

06:05.648 --> 06:06.289
God. But why do you say it should have had all of 
these things? Well, it was fighting for the

06:10.015 --> 06:12.279
dollars. But I mean, why do you think it should have 
been glamorized? Well, you call it glamorized,

06:15.625 --> 06:19.511
are we using the proper word? Maybe just say 
Department of Defense propaganda to

06:19.551 --> 06:27.283
indoctrinate the people of this country to accept 
it. To indoctrinate the... voters that the number

